"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709661","Department for Education","false","2017-03-17","<p>We know how important it is that children with medical conditions are supported to enjoy a full education. That is why we introduced a new duty to require governing bodies to make arrangements to support pupils with medical conditions and have provided statutory guidance outlining schools’ responsibilities in this area.</p><p> </p><p>We continue to work with Ofsted, and organisations such as the Health Conditions in Schools Alliance who have experience in supporting children with medical conditions, to help raise awareness of the duty.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-03-17T14:21:38.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709661/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709661/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-09","Children: Chronic Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to ensure schools have policies in place to look after children with medical conditions.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","67293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709662","Department for Education","false","2017-03-20","<p>The Education Funding Agency (EFA) will collect information on the condition of Second Consortium of Local Authorities (SCOLA) school buildings in Hampshire and North East Hampshire as part of the Condition Data Collection (CDC) programme. The CDC will run from 2017 to autumn 2019 and is a high-level, visual and non-invasive collection of consistent condition information for all government funded schools in England. It is the successor to the Property Data Survey (PDS) which collected condition information on the education estate between 2012 and 2014.</p><p>The CDC will assess the condition of school buildings and how they have changed since the PDS but it will not provide any assessment of the effect on educational provision or outcomes. The CDC will provide the EFA with an improved and up to date evidence base which will help inform future funding allocations and help direct investment to the areas with the greatest condition need. It will also help identify school buildings for inclusion in future rebuilding programmes and help those responsible for maintaining buildings develop their building management data.</p><p>In most cases, CDC condition information will be made available to a school and its responsible body within 8-10 weeks of the school’s site visit.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-03-20T09:52:29.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709662/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709662/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-09","Schools: Hampshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if the Government will make an assessment of the effect on educational (a) provision and (b) outcomes of the physical condition of the 1960s Second Consortium of Local Authorities schools in (i) Hampshire and (ii) North East Hampshire.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","67214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709663","Department for Education","false","2017-03-15","<p>We are committed to increasing the proportion of apprentices with a Black and Minority Ethnic background (BAME) by 20% by 2020, as part of the overall commitment to reach 3 million Apprenticeship starts in England.</p><p> </p><p>We have taken action through our current marketing campaign, ‘Get in Go Far’ to ensure that there is clear representation from apprentices from BAME backgrounds, including showcasing BAME apprentices in high status professional roles.</p><p> </p><p>On 21 February 2017 we launched the Apprenticeships Diversity Champions Network. This network, chaired by Nus Ghani MP, will be engaging and inspiring employers and communities to ensure that apprenticeships are represented by people from a diverse range of backgrounds, reflecting the widest spectrum of our society. The 23 members are committed to encouraging other employers to promote diversity in apprenticeships, and to championing apprenticeships in BAME communities.</p><p> </p><p>The National Careers Service provides information about learning and work, with a helpline giving professional advice on making the right choices, before and during apprenticeships.</p><p> </p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2017-03-15T16:49:36.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709663/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709663/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-09","Apprentices: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she plans to take to encourage people from Black and minority ethnic backgrounds to undertake apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","67229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709664","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-16","<p>The Government is investing £100,000 on a flood modelling study of Earby Beck to investigate options to reduce flood risk, with its results expected in October 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Environment Agency is carrying out works to repair and reduce the risk of blockage of the Victoria Clough culvert. Detailed design work is now complete and costs are estimated at £550,000.</p><p> </p><p>The Environment Agency has enhanced flood resilience in Earby by recruiting new flood wardens to support the development of a community flood plan and help coordinate the community response to future flood events. The Environment Agency is also investigating the installation of further rain gauges in the area to provide greater intelligence and accuracy to the flood warning service.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-03-16T12:29:50.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709664/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709664/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-09","Flood Control: Earby","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to increase flood prevention in Earby.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","67228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709665","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-16","<p>The Government Chief Scientific Adviser, Sir Mark Walport, intends to publish his third Annual Report, “From Waste to Resource Productivity”, co-authored by Professor Ian Boyd, Chief Scientific Adviser at Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, in the near future.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-03-16T17:28:36.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709665/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709665/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-09","Waste Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when her Chief Scientific Adviser plans to publish the report, From Waste to Resource Productivity.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","67234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709666","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-14","<p>In August 2016 the Government published its badger control costs for 2013 -2015. These can be found on the GOV.UK website under Bovine TB Government badger control costs 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The costs for the 2016 badger control operations are still to be finalised and will be published later this year.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-03-14T14:19:48.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709666/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709666/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-09","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much her Department has spent on administering badger control measures in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","67288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709667","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-14","<p>No direct comparison between the effectiveness of cage trapping and controlled shooting has been made. A combination of cage trapping and controlled shooting is the most efficient approach to obtain the required 70% population reduction to ensure disease control benefits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The numbers of badgers removed by cage trapping and controlled shooting in the cull areas in 2016 was published in December 2016.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-03-14T14:25:37.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709667/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709667/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-09","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment she has made of the relative effectiveness of cage trapping and controlled shooting in controlling badger populations.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","67289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709668","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-21","<p>The report on the comparison of the effect of the first two years of badger control in the first two areas is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/bovine-tb-incidence-of-tb-in-cattle-in-licensed-badger-control-areas-in-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/bovine-tb-incidence-of-tb-in-cattle-in-licensed-badger-control-areas-in-2014-to-2015</a></p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-03-21T12:11:56.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709668/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709668/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-09","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent assessment she has made of the levels of bovine TB in areas which are (a) under and (b) not under badger control measures.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","67290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709669","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-15","<p>Compensation for cattle which are compulsorily slaughtered for the purpose of controlling bovine TB in England is based on the actual market prices for 51 categories of bovines. Therefore, the total gross expenditure on compensation is the best measure of the value of those cattle, had they not been affected by the disease.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Total gross expenditure on compensation over the last five full financial years is set out below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total gross expenditure for cattle compulsorily slaughtered for the </strong> <strong>purpose of controlling bovine TB in England (£m)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>31.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>33.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>31.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>29.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>29.7</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-03-15T10:44:17.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709669/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709669/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-09","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate she has made of the total value of cattle slaughtered due to the detection of bovine TB within the herd in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","67291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709670","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-16","<p>In 2016 more than 29,000 cattle were compulsory slaughtered in England due to the discovery of bovine TB following surveillance testing. On average six reactors are found and slaughtered from testing where bovine TB is detected in a herd. As the comprehensive bovine TB testing surveillance regime ensures most bovine TB incidents are detected at an early stage, it is very rare for cattle herds to be fully slaughtered for bovine TB control reasons in England. There have been four such cases in England in the past five years.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year of incident</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Herd size</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>130</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>122 &amp; 25</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-03-16T12:46:51.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709670/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709670/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-09","Bovine Tuberculosis: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what information her Department holds on the largest single herds slaughtered due to the detection of bovine TB in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","67292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709671","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-17","<p>​We currently have fewer than ten colleagues on inward secondment to the FCO from a organisation outside the Civil Service. We do not confirm the precise numbers, or whether they are full or part-time staff, as this might enable individual identities to be revealed.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-03-17T14:31:34.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709671/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709671/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many (a) full-time and (b) part-time staff in his Department have been seconded from (i) businesses and (ii) charities.","true","Biography information for Susan Elan Jones","Clwyd South","Susan Elan Jones","67312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709672","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-17","<p>Details of Ministers' meetings with businesses and registered charities are published in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office's quarterly return on ministerial meetings with external organisations. The returns for the five years to September 2016, the most recent date for which information has been published, can be viewed here: <a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/minister-data" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/minister-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/minister-data</a></p><p>Details of officials' meetings with external organisations are not held centrally and to collate such information would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p /><p /><p /><p /><p />","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-03-17T14:46:04.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709672/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709672/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709672/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Meetings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many meetings (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have had with (i) businesses and (ii) registered charities in each of the last five years.","true","Biography information for Susan Elan Jones","Clwyd South","Susan Elan Jones","67320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709673","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-17","<p>​The UK is complying with its obligations under the Nuclear Non Proliferation Treaty (NPT).</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-03-17T14:17:40.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709673/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709673/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709673/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","Nuclear Disarmament","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether non-participation in the March 2017 UN Conference to Negotiate a Ban on Nuclear Weapons is compliant with the UK's obligations under the Non-Proliferation Treaty.","false","Biography information for Kate Hoey","Vauxhall","Kate Hoey","67267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709674","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-14","<p>I have met Foreign Minister Holguin on several occasions, most recently on 2 November 2016 during the State Visit of President Santos. We discussed progress in the Colombian peace process, likely challenges to its implementation, the Colombian Government’s approach to tackling human rights issues, and opportunities for further UK/Colombia cooperation.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-03-14T17:09:20.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709674/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709674/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709674/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","Colombia: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he last met his counterpart in the Republic of Colombia; and what issues were discussed at that meeting.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","67249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709675","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-14","<p>The Government has consistently raised prisoner payments at the highest levels with the Palestinian Authority and Palestine Liberation Organisation, and we continue to urge that these payments are more transparent, needs-based and affordable.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-14T16:13:24.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709675/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709675/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","Palestinians: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to the Palestinian Authority on alleged payments to convicted terrorists.","true","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","67242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709676","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-14","<p>Payments to Palestinian prisoners are made by the Palestinian Liberation Organisation, which has full administrative control for the monthly payments that are provided to prisoners’ families and ex-detainees. We have not made any assessment on the implications of these payments for the Middle East Peace Process.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-14T16:15:28.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709676/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709676/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","Palestinians: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the implications for the Middle East Peace Process of the alleged practice by the Palestinian Authority of paying salaries to convicted terrorists.","true","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","67243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709677","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-14","<p>​It is the longstanding policy of successive British Governments not to comment on intelligence matters. The Government deplores the leaking of any classified information, wherever it occurs. Such leaks can make the work of maintaining the security of our own country and that of our allies more difficult.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-03-14T17:11:12.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709677/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709677/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709677/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","USA: Intelligence Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the US Administration on the effect on UK security of leaks from US intelligence agencies.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","67364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709678","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-14","<p>The UK stands ready to support The Gambia and its new government. We are considering what assistance we can offer in support of human rights, democracy and the institutional and economic capacity of The Gambia. The UK is committed to supporting women and girls around the globe especially against the practice of female genital mutilation.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-14T16:17:46.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709678/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709678/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709678/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","Gambia: Female Genital Mutilation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he has taken to support the eradication of female genital mutilation in the Gambia since the election of President Adama Barrow.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","67370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709679","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-14","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to my answer of 9 March 2017 (PQ 66585).</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-03-14T15:00:25.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709679/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709679/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-09","Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to fulfil its UN Human Rights Council election pledge to protect and promote freedom of religion or belief.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","67342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709680","Department of Health","false","2017-03-15","<p>The Department has not yet determined how many Sustainability and Transformation Plan areas will receive the additional funding allocated in the Spring Budget.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","67287 ; 67387 ; 67388","2017-03-15T13:42:54.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709680/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709680/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what criteria were used to determine the first sustainable and transformation plan areas to receive Government funding.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","67323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709681","Department of Health","false","2017-03-16","<p>There are currently 79 high street dental practices in the prototype scheme testing a clinical pathway approach focussed on prevention as part of a possible new model of primary dental care. The scheme launched in 2016 and a list of the current dental prototypes can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/543919/Live_Prototype_List.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/543919/Live_Prototype_List.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The scheme is being evaluated under the oversight of an evidence and learning group, including external members and led by Professor Eric Rooney one of the two deputy Chief Dental Officers for England.</p><p> </p><p>The aim of reform is to improve oral health while maintaining access and delivering value for money. The evidence and learning group have identified the following five more detailed criteria against which to assess the success of the dental contract reform prototype scheme: access and accessibility, quality and appropriateness of care, improving oral health, value for money, scalability and potential roll-out. Dentists’ remuneration is a key part of assessing scalability and potential for wider roll out and also has its own programme reference group which includes representatives from the profession.</p><p>The main evaluation report is due by the end of this year with an initial report expected to be published later this spring.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","67337 ; 67339 ; 67343","2017-03-16T09:45:33.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709681/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709681/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","Dentistry: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the dental contract prototype on (a) patient oral health and (b) dentists' salaries and benefits.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","67341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709682","Department of Health","false","2017-03-16","<p>The additional capital investment budget available to the Department for Sustainability and Transformation Plans (STP) is £325 million spread equally over the years 2017-18 to 2019-20. The numbers shown in Table 2.1 of the Budget Document include Barnett consequentials for the devolved administrations.</p><p> </p><p>The amount of this investment as an overall proportion of the STP capital requirements is not clear as it will be partly covered by existing capital resources available in an STP area and their ability to raise receipts.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-03-16T10:31:50.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709682/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709682/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709682/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to page 26 of Budget 2017, how the £130 million in additional capital to sustainable and transformation plans (STPs) was calculated; and what proportion of the total capital requirement of STPs that represents.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","67324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709683","Department of Health","false","2017-03-14","<p>No such estimate has been made.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-03-14T11:02:13.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709683/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709683/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709683/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","Paramedical Staff: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the cost to the public purse of sickness absence in ambulance staff resulting from injuries sustained from physical violence at work from patients and members of the public.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","67359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709684","Department of Health","false","2017-03-16","<p>NHS England is responsible for commissioning dental services to meet local need. The Department does not routinely publish details of National Health Service funding for dental services as NHS England does not have a specified dental budget. There is no allocation specifically for dentistry, NHS England receives an overall primary care services budget which includes funding for all dental services.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-03-16T09:29:20.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709684/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709684/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709684/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","Dental Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, for what reasons his Department does not routinely publish details of NHS funding for dental services.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","67340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709685","Department of Health","false","2017-03-14","<p>The Government intends to lay the proposed Order before the Summer recess.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-03-14T10:51:29.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709685/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709685/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709685/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","Lone Parents: Surrogate Motherhood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 8 March 2017 to Question 66737, on surrogate motherhood and lone parents, when he plans to launch a consultation on legislative proposals to give single parents with children born through surrogacy the same rights as couples.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","67333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709686","Department of Health","false","2017-03-16","<p>There are currently 79 high street dental practices in the prototype scheme testing a clinical pathway approach focussed on prevention as part of a possible new model of primary dental care. The scheme launched in 2016 and a list of the current dental prototypes can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/543919/Live_Prototype_List.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/543919/Live_Prototype_List.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The scheme is being evaluated under the oversight of an evidence and learning group, including external members and led by Professor Eric Rooney one of the two deputy Chief Dental Officers for England.</p><p> </p><p>The aim of reform is to improve oral health while maintaining access and delivering value for money. The evidence and learning group have identified the following five more detailed criteria against which to assess the success of the dental contract reform prototype scheme: access and accessibility, quality and appropriateness of care, improving oral health, value for money, scalability and potential roll-out. Dentists’ remuneration is a key part of assessing scalability and potential for wider roll out and also has its own programme reference group which includes representatives from the profession.</p><p>The main evaluation report is due by the end of this year with an initial report expected to be published later this spring.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","67337 ; 67339 ; 67341","2017-03-16T09:45:33.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709686/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709686/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709686/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","Dental Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2016 to Question 47007, on dental services, which 79 high street practices are continuing to test the prevention-based clinical pathway.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","67343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709687","Department of Health","false","2017-03-14","<p>The proportion of specialist eating disorder beds provided by the private sector is 44% of adult beds and 75% of children’s beds, and of all specialist eating disorder beds 69% are private sector.</p><p> </p><p>The proportion of services delivered by the private sector is not collected centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-03-14T14:21:43.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709687/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709687/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709687/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","Eating Disorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proportion of eating disorder (a) beds and (b) services are delivered by the private sector.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","67347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709688","Department of Health","false","2017-03-16","<p>There are currently 79 high street dental practices in the prototype scheme testing a clinical pathway approach focussed on prevention as part of a possible new model of primary dental care. The scheme launched in 2016 and a list of the current dental prototypes can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/543919/Live_Prototype_List.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/543919/Live_Prototype_List.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The scheme is being evaluated under the oversight of an evidence and learning group, including external members and led by Professor Eric Rooney one of the two deputy Chief Dental Officers for England.</p><p> </p><p>The aim of reform is to improve oral health while maintaining access and delivering value for money. The evidence and learning group have identified the following five more detailed criteria against which to assess the success of the dental contract reform prototype scheme: access and accessibility, quality and appropriateness of care, improving oral health, value for money, scalability and potential roll-out. Dentists’ remuneration is a key part of assessing scalability and potential for wider roll out and also has its own programme reference group which includes representatives from the profession.</p><p>The main evaluation report is due by the end of this year with an initial report expected to be published later this spring.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","67339 ; 67341 ; 67343","2017-03-16T09:45:32.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709688/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709688/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709688/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","Dental Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Heal