"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709702","Department of Health","false","2017-03-14","<p>The Department will undertake a formal review of the Prime Minister’s Challenge on Dementia 2020 Implementation Plan in 2018. This review will be informed by the views of people with dementia, carers and seldom heard groups to assess whether the actions in the Implementation Plan are making a positive difference. The views of people with early onset dementia and their carers will be sought.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-03-14T11:38:06.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709702/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709702/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/709702/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-09","Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 6 March 2017 to Question 66177, on dementia, whether he plans to make an assessment of the adequacy of treatment provision for people diagnosed with early onset dementia.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","67248"
